problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-absolute-sum-of-any-subarray/description/

Intuition
Looking at this problem i realized this is a kadane pattern question but we need to return max absolute sum od any subarray , which can come through 2 best endings first with best ending at index i with max sum of subarray , second best ending with min sum of subarray at index i , the second best ending is justified as we take absolute of it so a negative best ending with higher magnitude becomes the result , we can take result as max of absolutes of both the endings

Approach
maxsumbestending is max (nums[i], maxsumbestending + nums[i])
minsumbestending is min of nums[i] , minsumbestending + nums[i]

result is max of (maxsumbestending , abs(minsumbestending) , result)

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)
Space complexity:
O(1)
Code
class Solution:
    def maxAbsoluteSum(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:
        maxsum_bestending = nums[0]
        minsum_bestending = nums[0]
        result = abs(nums[0])
        for i in range(1,len(nums)):
            v1 = nums[i]
            v2 = maxsum_bestending + nums[i]
            v3 = minsum_bestending + nums[i]

            maxsum_bestending = max(v1,v2)
            minsum_bestending = min(v1,v3)

            result = max(abs(maxsum_bestending) , abs(minsum_bestending),result)
        return result
